The paper deals with preference analysis, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the use of relational databases and the evaluation of queries suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of statistical ranking models and the development of solvers suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on hardness and the development of approximate solvers suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
